# Kung Fu Chess — Core Rules

## Stack

- C++17, STL only, no third-party deps
- Headers in `include/`, sources in `src/`
- Build: `.\build.bat` or CMake

## Code style

- Include guards: `#ifndef BOARD_H` / `#define BOARD_H` / `#endif`
- Classes: PascalCase (`Game`, `Board`); methods: camelCase (`handleClick`)
- Prefer `const` methods and references for read-only params
- Keep helpers as `static` functions in `.cpp` files when file-local

## Domain

- Cell tokens: `"."` empty; `"wK"`, `"bQ"` etc. — color (`w`/`b`) + piece (`KQRBNP`)
- `Board::CELL_SIZE = 100` — pixel coords map via `pixelToCell(x, y)`
- `Position`: `{ row, col }` with `isValid()` check

## Constraints

- Minimize diff scope; do not refactor unrelated code
- Do not add tests or docs unless requested
- Do not create git commits unless the user asks
